            "segment": "LINEAR EQUATIONS",
            "topic": "COLLEGE ALGEBRA",
            "code": "# slope_viz.py — Claude Code output\nm = 2          # slope of main line\n# rise/run triangle from (0,1)\nrun = 1; rise = m * run   # rise = 2\n\n# parallel: same slope\nm_par = m     # m_par = 2\n\n# perpendicular: negative reciprocal\nm_perp = -1/m  # m_perp = -0.5\n\n# key rule: m1 * m2 = -1\nassert m * m_perp == -1"
